reviewText: Many mistakes in the exercises. They have all been reported multiple times and being mentioned in the discussion forum for more than a year. No one is taking any action to correct them.The material is very dry just repeating the written content from the learn.microsoft.com website.
Time estimates were inaccurate, lab resources were often linked incorrectly, lab resources required corrections to function

Best course in the series so far, but the exercises were out of date and could be difficult to follow.  Some of the exercises aren't free- I've been doing the entire course in one shot so I've already burned through my $200 credit.  I was able to use a "free" trial of Databricks, though, so I was able to make it out for under $10 though.  It's doable- just be sure to delete your resources!   Databricks will still charge you for the VMs that it's set up on so if you want to get rid of those charges when you aren't using them, delete your databricks instance after you're done for the day.
G​readt course. gained more practicle knowledge
Muy bueno el curso de Microsoft Azure Databricks for Data Engineering, hace un repaso muy completo de los principales temas.
